    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 1 shows that knock-down of ephrin-B1 in cultured cortical neurons reduced ephB2-dependent syn-GFP (synaptophysin-GFP) accumulation on co-cultured HEK293 cells expressing EphB2. This supports a pre- and trans-synaptic role for ephrin-B1 in synapse assembly.\n\nFig 4 shows that knock-down of ephrin-B1 in cultured DIV21-23 cortical neurons results in reduced number of presynaptic puncta (syn-GFP), and of colocalized pre- and postsynaptic puncta.. Experimental description: Primary dissociated cortical neurons were prepared from embryonic day 17 (E17) to E18 rats",
